---
description: Repo-wide coding standards
globs: []
alwaysApply: true
---

- Strict typing everywhere — no `any` (TS) or untyped functions (Python)
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `test:`, `docs:`, `chore:`
- Prefer small, incremental changes
- Every new module must have corresponding tests
- Update `.context/progress.md` after completing tasks
- Reference `SPEC.md` for product requirements
- Do not create new top-level folders without updating ARCH.md
- Never commit session state files (`*.storage-state.json`) or credentials
- Tool names follow `{site}_{verb}_{noun}` convention (e.g., `linkedin_get_feed`)
- One browser process per authenticated domain — no cross-site session sharing
